content: So far so good, definately works better than Thingiverse itself. Is there an easy way to login to Thingiverse with a Google account. I keep going to the thingiverse login and it won't let you.

content: Fantastic app. Well worth supporting the devs for the experience. I always have more projects in the queue than I have time for because of this app.

3D Geeks makes browsing Thingiverse a pleasure. It adds missing features such as the ability to move items between collections. The only complaint I have is threading in comments a somewhat awkward to see and click through. Otherwise it is better in every way. The premium version was worth the cost to me both to support the developer and to access the extra features.
Does not work as intended
Purchased a key and everything worked great until the latest update. Stays in portrait view and crashes. Very disappointed.
replyContent: We have updated and fixed the app, please update the app from the play store for the fix

content: One word!! Outstanding.
Best app for STL files

What's with the censorship on this app? Refuses to show any models, or even the account, of colour3Djp.. though it does pop up with what appears to be their icon for a brief moment, it rapidly disappears, and shows none of his models, even when manually typed into search, which works 100% of the time either way on thingiverse.. edit: what else is censored in this app?
replyContent:
This user is known to publish NSFW content. Due to Google Play policies we are not allowed to show any nude or NSFW content. That's why NSFW content is completely blocked from 3D Geeks

Edit: NSFW and vulgar language

content: The apps is great, but it feels a bit weird that the adds are not disabled when the premium version is purchased. Also; is it possible to disable the "posted from 3d geeks app"-message? replyContent: Yes you can disable in the setting menu under comment signature and leave it empty. We understand your concern and will further investigate

replyContent: Thanks for letting us know! Will fix this issue asap!

content: It's great app if you get Premium, but you need to disable the ads, signature and watermarks manually after installing premium, which is a bit shady. Other than that, the app is great. Edit: I just wish I could change order of items in collections or change the size of the grid icons. Edit 2: I understand the need for advertising one's product, but it seems a bit excessive to me. Like above mentioned manual disabling the stuff, but also sharing a link doesn't just copy the link but also mentions the app with the emoji in its name, which kind of bugs me a bit too. So when sharing I have to delete that text before having a functional direct link.
replyContent:
Thank you for letting us know what you think. We understand your concerns, but as you said it is a way of advertising the product. Keeping an app up and running is not cheap, and there are bills that need to get paid. 

Edit: We have made changes to the share mechanism, please kill and restart the app twice, for the changes to take affect!
